</media>
<caption><emphasis effect="bold">General mechanism of a carbonyl <emphasis effect="italics">&#945;</emphasis>-substitution reaction.</emphasis> In step 3, the initially formed cation loses H<sup>+</sup> to regenerate a carbonyl compound.</caption>
